pageContext.claim: “Despite punishing society-wide lockdowns in Europe -- I don't know if you've been watching -- they're now experiencing a massive surge in cases. Daily cases are 2,500 percent higher in the United Kingdom, as an example, and 722 percent higher in Europe than in the United States.”
pageContext.analysis: No matter how much Trump tries to suggest Europe is doing worse than the United States in battling the coronavirus, the USA continues to do worse than virtually all of its peers. The United States never really ended its first wave -- and then quickly followed the European Union with even higher numbers in the fall-winter wave.
